					<div class="rightnote">
											</div>
					<div style="float:left;"><strong class="xar-sub">Subject:<a name="92100" href="http://www.ldonline.org/xarbb/topic/14007#92100">I so Desperately need info on Speed Processing
</a></strong></div>
					<div style="clear: both;"></div>
				</div>
				<div style="clear: left;">
															<p>Children with ADD tend to have compromised executive functioning which may make it difficult for them to prioritize and finish tasks on time. A lack of executive functioning skills can be accommodated for at schools by allowing for extra time on tests and assignments and giving step-by-step instructions on tasks. Tools such as graphic organizers can help children plan and organize better and complete their work on time.</p>
																				</div>
			</td>
